			"description": "Academic research is generally funded by the public so it is universally accepted that the outcomes should serve the public good. One way to carry out this duty is to transfer and develop applicable discoveries for the direct benefit of the public. The best mechanism for these types of transfers is through the private sector. In some instances new technology is best disseminated through the establishment of a new private company. The course will cover the basic steps of starting a biotechnology company. The instructor will use his own experience in launching a US biotech company as an example.",
