			"description": "The epistemological part of this module deals with topics such as the problem of stating the conditions for propositional knowledge, foundationalism and the coherence theory as an alternative, and scepticism and the responses to the sceptical problem. The part on metaphysics addresses the question of what it is to be a realist or an anti-realist with respect to a given subject-matter. The debate is followed across a range of topics such as meaning, truth, mind, the external world, universals, the past and future, modality, mathematics, conditionals and causes, and ethics. This course assumes some knowledge of formal and philosophical logic.",
